description:
Brief History

Battlejack's father was trapped on The Impericon by The Motivator and compelled to fight The Never Queen. Unfortunately for Battlejack and his father, his fight was short-lived.

After arriving on The Impericon, the Silver Surfer is shown Battlejack's terrible fight against the Never Queen by Zed. Having also been subjected to the effects of The Motivator, the Silver Surfer must prepare himself to face the Never Queen, lest he end up falling to the same fate as Battlejack.

Upon arriving in the depths of space near the Never Queen, the Silver Surfer takes Battlejack's armor and in an effort to disguise his identity. When he returns to The Impericon to save Dawn Greenwood in Battlejack's disguise, he comes face to face with Battlejack's father.

deck: A holy man for the Afghani Mujahideen who took control of the Gargoyle by imprisoning him by means of mystical pentagrams and commanded him using spells.
description:
Major Story Arcs

During a conflict with Manslaughter, Gargoyle suddenly disappears from the Defenders' base. They assume he was caught by Manslaughter, but actually he was summoned by a sorcerer in Afghanistan.

The sorcerer was able to summon Gargoyle because of his demon's body. He imprisons him in a flaming pentagram, and controls him with a pentagram of stone.

He demands that Gargoyle make gold, and to Gargoyle's surprise, he does.

The wizard is a Gnostic, and wants to use Gargoyle to rid the Earth of impurity. The wizard works for the Afghani Mujahideen, who barely tolerate him in their fight against the Soviets, who occupy Afghanistan at the time. He uses Gargoyle's power to defeat a Soviet attack. When the Mujahideen aren't impressed enough, he turns on them and kills them too. Then he goes to the Soviet command and tortures them, again using Gargoyle's magic--magic that Gargoyle himself didn't know he had.

Gargoyle tricks him into going to the United States, to gain riches. Gargoyle hopes to attract Dr. Strange's help, but the wizard realizes what he's doing. Disgusted by New York City, and seeing a billboard for Colorado, he goes there next.

The Defenders sense Gargoyle's presence nearby, and go to help him. They try to talk to the sorcerer, but he attacks them through Gargoyle. He thinks they are demons.

Beast eventually realizes that he is a Gnostic, and tries to distract him by talking with him using Gnostic terminology. The distraction doesn't last, and the battle continues. Finally they realize that he can't see well, and blind him with a flash of lightning bouncing off of Dragonfang. He then sees the Defenders as their true souls, most of which are pure and good, unlike the demons he thought they were, until he looks at Moondragon and Valkyrie, who he sees as Dragon and Death, and flees in terror. He breaks the pentagram that holds Gargoyle, who is freed.

He ends up cowering and nearly insane from his sight. They have some forest rangers pick him up and put him in custody as a mad vagrant.

Powers and Abilities

The Gnostic Wizard has at least some magical powers of his own: he is, for instance, able to summon Gargoyle's presence, and control him. However he seems to not be very magically skilled overall, and had many failures before summoning Isaac.

With Gargoyle's powers, he was capable of teleportation, creating a huge ghost hand with great strength, manipulating people's bodies as if they were clay, telepathy capable of breaking Moondragon's mind connection with Gargoyle, control of the elements, creating illusions, and other powerful effects.
name: Gnostic Wizard

deck: The Incredulous Zed appears to be the de-facto representative of The Impericon.
description:
Zed appears in space after the Silver Surfer is attacked by The Impericon's Gatekeepers. He seems friendly and affable towards the surfer and even shows him around The Impericon. Following the tour, Zed proposes Silver Surfer become The Impericon's Champion. The Motivator scans the Surfer, abducts Dawn Greenwood, and then Zed shows the surfer what happened to the previous champion of The Impericon who attempted to challenge the Never Queen.

While Zed spends most of his first appearance representing The Impericon to The Silver Surfer, he accepted counsel from another similarly dressed alien who was hidden in the shadows behind him. Time will only tell what Zed's true motivations are, what role he plays in The Impericon and just what it means for Silver Surfer to serve as a Champion.

Zed would later take the guise of Zee to be the apprentice of Glorian.

description:
JOSHUA BLACK is a dark comedy/fantasy series that follows a reluctant teenage deity, who inherits the throne of Heaven.

Joshua Black, created and written by Martin Dunn, is the story about a downtrodden high school student who is the next in line to inherit the throne of heaven. Along with his new found power, though, comes a great burden. This story follows Joshua as he learns to wield his powers responsibly, and eventually becomes the God that he was meant to be.

Name: Joshua Black
Aliases: Josh, Monkey
Occupation: Student
Classification: God
Place of Birth: Trinity, Florida
Known Relatives: Joseph Black, Mary Black, Jessica Black
Height: 5’11
Weight: 182
Hair: Black
Eyes: Brown/ Blue
D.O.B. July 24,1996
Gender: Male
Sexual Orientation: Heterosexual
First Appearance: Joshua Black: The Divine Hierarchy #1
Status: *RESURRECTED*

Bio:
Joshua Black was born in Trinity, Florida, where his mother and father raised him until he was six years old. Shortly after his birthday his mother was killed in a car accident. Joshua, who had distracted his mother, always felt guilty about her death. His guilt was made worse by his father, who reminded him regularly that if it weren’t for him, Mary and her unborn child would be alive. Joshua learned to block out a lot of the abuse and even pitied his father. He refused to raise a hand to him, because he believed that the man had suffered enough. His unwillingness to fight back often led to bumps and bruises and had even resulted in a couple of broken bones over the years. One day, though, Joe hit Josh harder than he’d meant to, causing his neck to break as his body slammed against the bathtub.
As part of a divine hierarchy, Joshua was not expected to die in such a mundane way. His death threw heaven into chaos, causing the angels to panic. They set time back, hoping to undo the damage that had been done by Josh’s early demise. They were unaware, however, that Joshua’s mother was meant to die and his unborn sister was never meant to be born. Josh awoke the morning after he broke his neck to find his mother and sister alive. No one but him seemed to realize anything was amiss. Joshua was soon confronted by angels who explained the situation. He also learned that some of the people who he had known for years had been lying to him about who they were and what their motives were.
Soon after discovering his place in the hierarchy and learning about his powers, Joshua met a girl named Levetica. While he initially found her terrifying, he soon came to think of her as a friend, realizing that he could share things in his life with her that neither his longtime girlfriend Tracy, nor his best friend Pete would understand. While Josh had never felt like Tracy completely understood him, he had recently come to see that she expected things of him that he wasn't sure he wanted to give. He had also started to feel that his relationship with Pete was strained, and while he couldn't quite figure out the reason, Josh could tell that the dynamics of their friendship had begun to shift. While it was clear from the beginning that Levetica had a lot of flaws, he felt comfortable around her and appreciated the simplicity of his time with her.
name: Joshua Black
